<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<nobr><h2 class="h2view">About Advanced Monolithic Systems</h2></nobr>
</td></tr></table><br>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="950" align="left" id="gptMfg" class="main" style="font-size:16px;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:25px;"><tr><td>
Advanced Monolithic Systems (AMS) is a semiconductor company that specializes in the design and manufacturing of analog and mixed-signal integrated circuits (ICs). The company was founded in 1989 and is headquartered in San Diego, California.<br><br>AMS offers a wide range of IC products, including voltage references, operational amplifiers, comparators, and analog switches. These products are used in a variety of applications, including automotive, communications, consumer electronics, and industrial automation.<br><br>AMS is known for its high-quality products and commitment to innovation. The company's ICs are designed to meet the highest standards of performance and reliability, and are manufactured using the latest technology and materials. AMS also offers custom design and engineering services to meet the specific needs of its customers.<br><br>AMS has a global presence, with sales offices and representatives located around the world. The company also maintains partnerships with a number of leading electronics manufacturers, ensuring that its products are available to customers worldwide.<br><br>
*This information is for general informational purposes only, we will not be liable for any loss or damage caused by the above information.
</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table>
